The paper deals with image super-resolution, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of optimization techniques and interpolation methods also suggests that it could belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of fractional-order gradient interpolation and reconstruction could also suggest that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
